						<summary>

						<p>On two faces of a slab lying in the courtyard of the Chennakēśavasvāmin temple.</p>						

						<p>Kṛishṇarāya, 1517 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is badly damaged. Mentions Śāḷuva Tipi and Sāḷuva Komāra Timarasayya in whose presence Timmapa seems to have demarcated some forest land obviously granted for some purpose. The cyclic year <hi rend="bold">Īśvara</hi> which seems to be quoted in the record corresponds to <hi rend="bold">1517 A.D.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
